record.detail: A soldier at Wynyard Square oversees the AWA tower which was illuminated for the first time for years in honour of VE Day in 1945. The tower is now illuminated every evening and its geometric design was a fitting backdrop for the helicopter escape scene in the science fiction film, The Matrix, in 1999.

record.title: recall
record.detail: The AWA tower had been subject to the same 'brown out' rules as the rest of the city during the war but on the night of 8 May 1945 it was floodlit, along with other buildings in the centre of the city, as part of the VE Day celebrations that marked the end of the war in Europe.
